-- Indian shares gain for fourth straight session; auto stocks surge
-- By Indulal PM
-- Wed Oct 22, 2014 06:14AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, Oct 22 (Reuters) - Indian shares gained for a fourth consecutive session on Wednesday, closing at their highest level in a month as blue chips climbed, tracking stronger global markets, while auto stocks surged on hopes of better sales in the festive season.

The benchmark BSE index <.BSESN> provisionally closed 0.8 percent higher at 26,787.23, while the broader NSE index <.NSEI> advanced 0.86 percent to 7,995.90.